<section class="section" aria-labelledby="platform-title">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div><div class="eyebrow">01 · PLATFORM</div><h2 id="platform-title">Built to work.<br><span>Designed to move.</span></h2></div>
    <p>Motion communicates state, depth directs attention, and every interface still has a practical purpose. Nothing calls itself “live” merely because it rendered.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">01 / COMMAND</span>
      <h3>Website audit</h3>
      <p>Inspect titles, descriptions, canonicals, headings, indexing, social metadata, and HTTPS without sending retrieved page content into a model.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--optional">Worker tool</span><a class="card__link" href="/command/">Open Command →</a></div>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">02 / FIGHT CLUB</span>
      <h3>Compare responses</h3>
      <p>Give two contenders the same task, see the exact runtime provider behind each answer, then judge the result locally.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--optional">Provider-aware</span><a class="card__link" href="/challenge/">Start a round →</a></div>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">03 / SWARM</span>
      <h3>Orchestrate a mission</h3>
      <p>Move one objective through strategist, builder, critic, and closer roles with every engine and fallback made visible.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--optional">Worker enhanced</span><a class="card__link" href="/swarm/">Deploy swarm →</a></div>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">04 / ATLAS ID</span>
      <h3>Own your profile</h3>
      <p>Create an operator card that remains in your browser. Export it as JSON and import it elsewhere—there is no imaginary cloud sign-in.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--local">Local only</span><a class="card__link" href="/atlas-id/">Build an ID →</a></div>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">05 / ARENA</span>
      <h3>Study exhibitions</h3>
      <p>Browse curated model matchups as an editorial archive. Scores and records are presented as demonstrations, never live telemetry.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--demo">Editorial demo</span><a class="card__link" href="/arena/">View archive →</a></div>
    </article>
    <article class="card" data-tilt>
      <span class="card__index">06 / SOURCE</span>
      <h3>Inspect the system</h3>
      <p>The source tree, Worker routes, provider contract, security controls, tests, and deployment requirements live together.</p>
      <div class="card__footer"><span class="status-chip status-chip--local">Source available</span><a class="card__link" href="{{ platform.repository }}">View repository →</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="truth-layer" aria-labelledby="truth-title">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div><div class="eyebrow">02 · TRUTH LAYER</div><h2 id="truth-title">One label.<br><span>One meaning.</span></h2></div>
    <p>The platform has four public states. The label comes from behavior, not presentation.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="truth-grid">
    <article class="truth-item"><span class="status-chip status-chip--live">Live</span><h3>Server verified</h3><p>A current request completed and returned the expected response contract.</p></article>
    <article class="truth-item"><span class="status-chip status-chip--local">Local</span><h3>Browser only</h3><p>Data and behavior stay on this device unless you explicitly export them.</p></article>
    <article class="truth-item"><span class="status-chip status-chip--demo">Demo</span><h3>Editorial</h3><p>Curated content illustrates an interface; it is not represented as a provider call.</p></article>
    <article class="truth-item"><span class="status-chip status-chip--optional">Optional</span><h3>Configuration bound</h3><p>The feature activates only when its required server-side binding is present.</p></article>
  </div>
</section>

